  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='black' class='header'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>THE SKINNY ON BOTR</font>, By Obiden starwalker</b><br><br>This is a quest. I've done this quest a couple-o-dozen times. The belt is HFL only so the info above is wrong. The Belt is probably somewhat rare as only HFL's would be interested in it. The same quest can yield the Wee Harvestor, a Druid only 2H blunt. So, here are the steps for the quest:

1) Find Nomsoe in the Temple of Life in Qeynos and say &#34;I will take the flask&#34; or talk to him until you get a flask of blessed oil.

2) Search the Miller's corn fields in West Karana for a bag of hay. It takes some running around sometimes, but eventually you can find one laying on the ground.

3) Find Roror in Feerott. Stay right when you enter the zone from Rathe Mts. Roror can be found in the area between the road / river / zone wall's East&South. Roror usually pauses at the rivers edge near the zone wall. Hail him (he's a quest NPC so indifferent to all). Give him 66g and the hay and in return you get a bit of exp and a sack of cursed hay. 

4) In Rivervale procede to the forge near the farm/druid guild. Combine the flask of oil and the sack of cursed hay in the forge. Some say you need at least a skill of 21 in smithing, some say you don't. I got my skill to 22 for the 1st couple of times I did the quest and never failed the combine. The forge combine yields a sack of writhing hay.

5) Give the sack of writhing hay Shakey the Scarecrow. In return you recieve the Belt of the River or the Wee Harvester.

As I said I did the quest about 30 times. The last time I did it I got the Harvester. I sold about 23 or 24 belts, gave 3 or 4 away and kept one on my Druid. Cost was say about 200pp and the time to travel. At an average selling price of 40pp I made about 1000pp - 200pp for a net of about 800pp. The avg time spent on the quest non-stop is about 2 hours (depending on Roror being available) with SoW. It can be days if Roror is not spawning because you certainly don't want to hang about Feerott very long as a mid-level player. Only thing to do there is newbie mobs or Spec's and Bouncers.
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
